<form>: the tag acts as a conatainer for all input fields.
       it often includes an action attributes,which specifies where to send the form data  upon submission.
<labels> used to identify input fields for the user.

type="text":for standard short text
type="email":specially for email address
type="password":masks the characters typed for security.
type="radio":used for multiple choice questions where only one option can be selected.


essential attributes

id:A unique identifier for the element ,used for linking labels and hooks for CSS/java script.

name:critical for server side processing to identify which piece of datacorresponds to which field.

value:defines data sent to the server,especially important for radio buttons and  dropdowns where the user isn't typing their own text.

